# ============================================================================
# _melrose — zsh completion for melrose, interactive MIDI melody programming
# ============================================================================
#
# UPSTREAM
#   Repository : https://github.com/emicklei/melrose
#   Author     : Ernest Micklei (emicklei — long-time Go community member,
#                author of go-restful and proto)
#   License    : MIT
#   Stars      : 209
#   Language   : Go
#   Module     : github.com/emicklei/melrose  (Go 1.25.0)
#   Binary     : melrose  (built from cmd/melrose/main.go)
#   Last push  : 2026-04-17
#
# WHAT IT IS
#   melrose is "interactive programming of melodies, producing MIDI" — Ernest
#   Micklei's Go DSL for composing music in a live REPL.  Users define
#   notes, chords, sequences, loops, and patterns in a small expression
#   language built on `expr-lang/expr` (e.g. `notes('C D E F')`, `sequence(...)`,
#   `loop(s, bpm=120)`), and melrose schedules them through the
#   `gitlab.com/gomidi/midi/v2` library to the host's MIDI output device.
#   The CLI starts a tiny HTTP server on `:8118` so VS-Code / Emacs / editor
#   plugins can post DSL snippets and trigger immediate playback, while
#   simultaneously dropping the terminal into an interactive REPL backed by
#   peterh/liner with history and tab completion.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from system/setup.go + server/lang.go
#                       Go stdlib `flag` declarations — single-dash long form)
#   melrose [FLAGS]
#
#   Flags (Go stdlib `flag` package — both `-name` and `--name` accepted;
#   `-` is the conventional form):
#     -d                       Debug logging
#     -log <PATH>              Error log file location (created if absent)
#     -http <ADDR>             HTTP listen address for the editor-plugin
#                              endpoint                  [default: ":8118"]
#     -h, -help                Show help (Go flag stdlib auto)
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `gitlab.com/gomidi/midi/v2 v2.3.18` declared in
#   go.mod — the canonical Go MIDI library by Marc René Arns (gitlab.com/
#   gomidi).  gomidi/midi provides cross-platform MIDI I/O (rtmidi backend
#   bridging ALSA RawMidi on Linux, CoreMIDI on macOS, WinMM on Windows)
#   plus SMF (Standard MIDI File) reading / writing and a comprehensive
#   message-type tree.  melrose's `midi/transport` and `midi/registry`
#   packages wrap gomidi/midi to enumerate ports, open output devices,
#   and emit timed NoteOn / NoteOff sequences.  Verified via:
#     gh api repos/emicklei/melrose/contents/go.mod
#       → gitlab.com/gomidi/midi/v2 v2.3.18
#   This entry is the Go=118 leader bump that continues Axis 63
#   (MIDI I/O Library) opened at R841 with Rust=midir (devaloop-labs/
#   devalang).
#
#   No completion for `melrose` ships with Apple zsh
#   (/usr/share/zsh/*/functions) or Homebrew zsh-completions
#   (/opt/homebrew/share/zsh/site-functions) — confirmed absent.
# ============================================================================

_melrose() {
    _arguments \
        '-d[debug logging]' \
        '-log[error log file location]:log file:_files' \
        '-http[HTTP listen address (default :8118)]:listen addr:' \
        '(- *)-h[show help]' \
        '(- *)-help[show help]'
}

_melrose "$@"
